# Playwright Test Suite

This repository contains automated **UI and API tests** using Playwright.  
It covers testing of [FakeStore API](https://fakestoreapi.com/) and [Restful-Booker API](https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/), as well as any UI interactions you may add.

---

## Project Structure

tests/
‚îú‚îÄ api/ # API test files
‚îî‚îÄ ui/ # UI test files


- `api/` - contains tests for GET, POST, PUT, DELETE requests.
- `ui/` - contains tests for user interface interactions, if applicable.

---

## Setup

1. **Clone the repository**

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <repo-folder>

Install dependencies

npm install

Install Playwright browsers

npx playwright install


Running Tests

Run all tests

npx playwright test

Run only API tests

npx playwright test tests/api

Run only UI tests

npx playwright test tests/ui

Run a specific test file

npx playwright test tests/api/booking.spec.js


Run in headed mode (see browser interactions)

npx playwright test --headed

Run with debug logs

npx playwright test --debug

### üìä Test Reporting (Playwright HTML Report)

This project uses Playwright to generate a detailed, interactive HTML report after each test run. This report provides deep insights, error messages, and artifacts (like screenshots and videos) for failed tests.

**To view the latest generated report:**

1.  **Install Dependencies:** Ensure all necessary packages are installed.
    
    npm install
    
2.  **Run the Tests:** Execute your test script (which generates the report files).
  
    npm run test:ui:report 
    # Or your basic test command: npx playwright test

3.  **Open the Report in Browser:** Use the Playwright CLI command to launch the report on a local server.
   
    npx playwright show-report

This command will automatically open the full, interactive report in your default web browser.

